In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture. Stir in cracker crumbs and ground pecans; mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Place a pecan half in the center of each cookie; press down lightly. Bake at 350 degrees F for 9-11 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks.